A newspaper is an important publication that is published for the people. It carries all the latest news and views on various issues happening around us.

Stories and reports published in newspapers are of news items that are local, national as also global. We are influenced and affected by happenings around us whether these are in our neighborhood, in our own towns or cities, our country or the world. And so it is important to know what is happening around us.

Events and issues are reported by journalists also known as reporters and correspondents. They go to the scene of action and file authentic, wholly true and error-free news and reports that are published in the newspapers. There are also well-known experts and personalities who write for newspapers. They analyze various situations and issues that affect us. They help us understand situations better and form opinions. Stories in newspapers have bylines of writers and authors.

A number of newspapers are brought out in many different languages around the country so that the public may easily access news. It helps us know about life around us.
